==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puccoon
<hw>Puc*coon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the American
Indian name.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any one of several plants
yielding a red pigment which is used by the North American Indians, as
the bloodroot and two species of <gen>Lithospermum</gen>
(<spn>Lithospermum hirtum</spn>, and <spn>Lithospermum canescens</spn>);
also, the pigment itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puce</ent>⟦br⟧
